Sentiment Dictionary¶

Using OpinionFinder_Lexicon to prepare dictionary to use as sentiment score. Score will be:

  1. Weak Positive = 1
  2. Weak Negative = -1
  3. Strong Positive = 3
  4. Strong Negative = -3
In [94]:
#Sentiment 
senti = open('OpinionFinder_Lexicon.tff','r').read().splitlines()

sentiment = {}

for line in senti:
  tokens = line.split(' ')

  term = tokens[2].replace('word1=','')

  if tokens[0] == 'type=weaksubj':
    score =1
  elif tokens[0]== 'type=strongsubj':
    score =3

  if tokens[5] == 'priorpolarity=negative':
    polarity = -1
  elif tokens[5] == 'priorpolarity=positive':
    polarity = 1

  sentiment[term] = polarity * score


df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(sentiment,orient='index')

import csv

with open('sentiment.csv', 'w') as f:
  w= csv.writer(f)
  w.writerows(sentiment.items())

Separate each review into token and give it a score based on each word¶

  • Sentiment score of more than 0 is positive
  • Sentiment score of less than 0 is negative
In [98]:
listoflists = []
def calculate_sentiment(d,side):
  import re
  tokens = re.findall(r'\w+', d.lower())
  sentiment_score=0
  #print(condition)
  for token in tokens:
    if token in sentiment:
      sentiment_score = sentiment_score + sentiment[token]
      if (sentiment_score > 0 and side =='good'):
        return token    
      elif (sentiment_score < 0 and side =='bad'):
        return token    
      if (side=='all'):
        if (sentiment_score > 0):
          grade = 'positive'
        else:
          grade = 'negative'
        return [token,sentiment[token],grade]
  if (side==''):
    return sentiment_score

  • Negative

all = []

for val in df.Review:
  words = calculate_sentiment(val,'all')
  if words is None:
    continue
  else:
    all.append(words)
